WEBVTT

00:24.942 --> 00:26.944
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTERING ON RADIO)</font>

01:00.102 --> 01:03.147
<font color="#808080">TAYLOR:</font> Neighbors heard them screaming
at each other, like, for two hours.

01:03.314 --> 01:05.483
Nothing new. Then they
heard the gun go off.

01:05.649 --> 01:06.817
Both barrels.

01:08.152 --> 01:10.237
A crime of passion.

01:10.571 --> 01:12.073
Yeah.

01:12.239 --> 01:14.825
Just look at all the
passion on that wall.

01:14.992 --> 01:17.912
<font color="#808080">TAYLOR:</font> Yeah, well, this is a done deal.
All but the paperwork.

01:22.208 --> 01:23.542
The kid see it?

01:23.709 --> 01:25.127
<font color="#808080">TAYLOR:</font>
What?

01:25.377 --> 01:26.962
The kid.

01:27.213 --> 01:28.839
What kind of fucking
question is that?

01:29.006 --> 01:30.049
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font>

01:30.216 --> 01:34.470
We are all gonna be real glad when we get
rid of you, Somerset, you know that?

01:34.845 --> 01:37.681
There's always these questions
with you. Did the kid see it?

01:37.848 --> 01:40.392
Who gives a fuck? He's dead.
His wife killed him.

01:40.851 --> 01:43.354
Anything else has nothing
to do with us.

01:43.521 --> 01:45.314
<font color="#D900D9">(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)</font>

01:51.779 --> 01:53.864
Detective Somerset?

01:55.199 --> 01:56.992
I'm Detective Mills.

01:57.159 --> 01:59.578
<font color="#808080">MILLS:</font> Lieutenant, I apologize
for interrupting like this...

01:59.745 --> 02:02.373
...just get in town 20 minutes ago,
they dump me here.

02:02.540 --> 02:03.958
Look, um...

02:04.291 --> 02:05.501
Mills?

02:05.668 --> 02:08.378
I thought we might
find a bar someplace. Sit, talk...

02:08.545 --> 02:10.422
I'd like to get to the precinct.

02:10.589 --> 02:13.676
You know, not much time
for this transition thing.

02:14.677 --> 02:17.596
I meant to ask you something,
when we spoke on the phone before.

02:17.763 --> 02:18.973
Yeah.

02:20.224 --> 02:21.725
Why here?

02:21.892 --> 02:23.561
I don't follow.

02:23.727 --> 02:26.772
Well, all this effort
to get transferred.

02:27.731 --> 02:30.693
It's the first question
that popped into my head.

02:31.026 --> 02:32.736
I guess for the same
reasons as you.

02:32.903 --> 02:36.115
Or the same reasons you had
before you decided to quit, yeah?

02:37.992 --> 02:40.202
You just met me.

02:40.870 --> 02:43.414
Maybe I'm not understanding
the question.

02:44.456 --> 02:46.208
It's very simple.

02:46.709 --> 02:50.754
You actually fought
to get reassigned here.

02:51.255 --> 02:53.299
I've just never seen it done
that way before.

02:53.465 --> 02:55.885
I thought I could do some good.
It would be great...

02:56.051 --> 02:58.762
...if we didn't start out
kicking each other in the balls.

02:58.929 --> 03:00.181
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

03:01.265 --> 03:03.934
- If you're calling the shots, lieutenant...
- Yes.

03:05.060 --> 03:08.314
I want you to look
and I want you to listen, okay?

03:08.480 --> 03:10.941
Now, I wasn't standing around
guarding the Taco Bell.

03:11.108 --> 03:13.194
- I've worked Homicide five years.
- Not here.

03:13.360 --> 03:14.403
I understand that.

03:14.570 --> 03:19.116
Well, over the next seven days, detective,
you'll do me the favor of remembering that.

03:30.878 --> 03:33.631
<font color="#808080">MAN 1:</font>
Hey, hey. I almost died.

03:38.344 --> 03:40.346
<font color="#D900D9">(TICKING)</font>

03:45.976 --> 03:48.979
<font color="#D900D9">(MEN ARGUING INDISTINCTLY)</font>

03:57.029 --> 03:59.240
<font color="#808080">MAN 2:</font>
Shut the fuck up down there!

06:19.296 --> 06:22.383
<font color="#D900D9">(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)</font>

06:43.821 --> 06:47.324
<font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLING)</font>

07:01.672 --> 07:03.215
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGS)</font>

07:03.382 --> 07:05.384
Hello? Yeah.

07:05.551 --> 07:06.969
Okay.

07:07.886 --> 07:09.388
Say it again.

07:11.974 --> 07:15.686
I thought we moved here
to get away from tractor pulls.

07:15.853 --> 07:17.855
<font color="#D900D9">(MILLS CHUCKLES)</font>

07:20.023 --> 07:21.024
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

07:21.191 --> 07:23.318
Serpico's gotta go.

07:23.485 --> 07:27.364
Yeah, well, you might wanna get rid
of this little crusty.

07:27.531 --> 07:29.158
This eye, Serpico.

07:29.324 --> 07:30.784
- Did you get it?
- Got it.

07:30.951 --> 07:32.286
Good.

07:44.715 --> 07:46.091
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

07:48.677 --> 07:50.012
Coffee?
No?

07:54.475 --> 07:57.561
<font color="#808080">DAVIS:</font> Nothing's been touched.
Everything's like I found it.

07:57.728 --> 07:59.396
<font color="#808080">SOMERSET:</font>
What time was death established?

07:59.563 --> 08:01.064
<font color="#808080">DAVIS:</font>
Like I said...

08:01.231 --> 08:02.566
...I didn't touch anything.

08:03.317 --> 08:06.737
But he's had his face in a plate of
spaghetti for about 45 minutes now.

08:06.904 --> 08:09.656
<font color="#808080">MILLS:</font> Wait a minute.
No one bothers with vital signs?

08:09.823 --> 08:10.991
<font color="#808080">DAVIS:</font>
Did I stutter?

08:11.158 --> 08:14.536
This guy ain't breathing unless he
started breathing spaghetti sauce.

08:14.703 --> 08:18.023
- <font color="#808080">MILLS:</font> So that's how it's done around here?
- <font color="#808080">DAVIS:</font> I beg your pardon, detective.

08:18.081 --> 08:21.084
But this guy's been sitting
in a pile of his own piss and shit.

08:21.251 --> 08:23.420
If he wasn't dead,
he would've stood up by now.

08:23.587 --> 08:25.756
All right, thank you, officer.
Okay.

08:26.089 --> 08:27.758
Thank you.

08:37.267 --> 08:38.852
I wonder.

08:40.938 --> 08:45.067
What exactly was the point of the
conversation you were about to get into?

08:45.234 --> 08:46.276
<font color="#808080">MILLS:</font>
Don't know.

08:46.443 --> 08:50.364
How many times has Barney Fife
found dead bodies that weren't dead?

08:51.907 --> 08:53.408
Drop it.

08:55.285 --> 08:57.162
<font color="#D900D9">(MILLS SNIFFS)</font>

09:18.642 --> 09:19.643
Oof.

09:23.272 --> 09:27.359
Somebody phone Guinness.
I think we've got a record here.

09:43.750 --> 09:46.128
<i>Better Homes and Gardens.</i>

09:46.295 --> 09:47.504
<font color="#D900D9">(SNIFFS)</font>

09:47.671 --> 09:48.672
Oof.

09:56.722 --> 09:58.181
Who said this was murder?

09:58.765 --> 10:00.225
No one.

10:02.019 --> 10:05.522
Guy's heart's gotta be the size
of a canned ham.

10:08.191 --> 10:13.989
If this isn't a coronary,
well, ha, ha, I don't know.

10:30.714 --> 10:32.841
Whoops.

10:39.181 --> 10:41.350
How about that?

10:51.234 --> 10:52.986
We had this case once.

10:54.112 --> 10:56.031
Guy dead on the ground.

10:56.198 --> 10:57.366
Knife in his back.

10:57.532 --> 10:59.576
Gotta be murder, right?

11:01.370 --> 11:02.412
Fuck.

11:03.246 --> 11:05.791
Anyway,
big insurance policy involved, yeah?

11:05.957 --> 11:10.671
So the guy took the tip of the blade,
stuck it in his own shoulder blades.

11:10.837 --> 11:14.508
And he must've screwed up a few times
because there was multiples back there.

11:14.675 --> 11:16.593
Could you please be quiet?

11:26.103 --> 11:27.145
<font color="#808080">MILLS:</font>
Wait a minute.

11:27.479 --> 11:28.689
What?

11:31.316 --> 11:33.235
Got a bucket here.

11:33.902 --> 11:34.945
What's in it?

11:38.490 --> 11:39.825
Agh!

11:39.991 --> 11:41.910
Oh, God.

11:42.077 --> 11:43.704
Fucking vomit.

11:43.870 --> 11:46.039
<font color="#D900D9">(BLOWING NOSE)</font>

11:46.206 --> 11:47.290
Any blood in it?

11:47.999 --> 11:50.502
I didn't see any.
Help yourself.

11:50.669 --> 11:52.421
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

11:55.632 --> 11:57.634
Are you thinking it's poison?

11:58.802 --> 12:01.179
<font color="#808080">O'NEILL:</font>
Oh, wonderful. Very moody.

12:01.346 --> 12:02.973
Thinking it's poison, Somerset?

12:03.140 --> 12:06.601
You girls have got Forensics
waiting outside.

12:06.768 --> 12:10.689
Don't know if we'll all fit, though.
There's room, light's the problem.

12:10.856 --> 12:12.649
- Hi, how are you?
- Hey.

12:12.816 --> 12:17.112
Detective Mills, would you go help
the officers question the neighbors?

12:19.656 --> 12:22.325
- What?
- Send in Forensics on your way out, please.

12:38.175 --> 12:39.968
He's dead.

12:41.052 --> 12:43.013
Thank you, doctor.

12:44.264 --> 12:46.266
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTERING ON RADIO)</font>

12:48.643 --> 12:52.189
You've seen my files, right?
You seen the things I've done.

12:52.355 --> 12:53.815
Nope.

12:56.234 --> 12:58.653
I did my time on door-to-doors
and walking the beat.

12:58.820 --> 13:01.156
I did that shit for a long time.

13:01.990 --> 13:03.033
And?

13:03.200 --> 13:06.536
Badge on my belt says "detective."
That's the same as yours.

13:07.954 --> 13:10.415
Look, I made a decision.

13:10.707 --> 13:13.418
I had to consider
the integrity of the scene.

13:13.585 --> 13:17.297
Couldn't worry whether you thought you
were getting enough on the playing field.

13:17.464 --> 13:18.840
Hey, man...

13:20.091 --> 13:23.595
...just don't be jerking me off,
that's all I ask. Don't jerk me off.

13:30.268 --> 13:31.937
He's been dead a long time.

13:32.103 --> 13:34.147
And I can tell you,
it was not from poison.

13:34.314 --> 13:35.482
<font color="#808080">MILLS:</font>
Oh, man.

13:35.649 --> 13:37.818
How does someone
let themselves go like that?

13:38.360 --> 13:41.571
<font color="#808080">SANTIAGO:</font> It took four orderlies
just to get him on the table.

13:42.656 --> 13:44.241
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

13:44.407 --> 13:46.785
How'd the fat fuck
ever fit out his front door?

13:46.952 --> 13:48.954
Please.
It's obvious he was a shut-in.

13:49.120 --> 13:50.539
<font color="#808080">SANTIAGO:</font>
Now, look at this.

13:50.705 --> 13:52.249
See how big this stomach is?

13:52.415 --> 13:55.252
And the strange thing is,
it stretches.

13:55.418 --> 13:58.630
Here. Look at the size of the
cardiac orifice, where the food...

13:58.797 --> 14:01.883
Wait, I see what you're pointing out,
but that means nothing to me.

14:02.050 --> 14:05.512
Okay. He's got lines of distention
across the duodenum.

14:05.929 --> 14:08.598
And the interior
wall is ripped open.

14:09.099 --> 14:11.268
This man ate till he burst?

14:11.434 --> 14:13.937
He didn't really burst.
Not all the way.

14:14.104 --> 14:16.565
He was hemorrhaging internally.

14:16.731 --> 14:20.944
And there was a hematoma in the rectus
and transverse abdominis muscles.

14:21.111 --> 14:22.445
So he did die by eating.

14:22.612 --> 14:24.155
Yes and no.

14:26.157 --> 14:27.868
What about these
bruises up here?

14:29.786 --> 14:31.538
Well, I haven't
figured that out yet.

14:31.913 --> 14:33.582
Gun pressed against his head?

14:33.748 --> 14:35.083
Pressed hard enough, sure.

14:35.250 --> 14:36.710
Fuck, yeah.

14:36.877 --> 14:39.796
Marks from the front side,
flush with the muzzle.

14:41.673 --> 14:45.385
Ladies and gentlemen,
we have ourselves a homicide.

14:48.054 --> 14:50.807
<font color="#808080">SOMERSET:</font> Killer put a bucket
beneath him, kept on serving.

14:50.974 --> 14:52.350
Took his time, too.

14:52.517 --> 14:55.270
Coroner said this could've gone on
more than 12 hours.

14:55.729 --> 14:58.732
Victim's throat was swollen,
probably from the effort.

14:58.899 --> 15:01.776
And there was definitely a point
when he passed out.

15:01.943 --> 15:04.487
That's when the killer kicked him
and he burst.

15:04.654 --> 15:06.615
Oof.
Sadistic fucker, huh?

15:06.781 --> 15:09.221
<font color="#808080">SOMERSET:</font> When you want somebody
dead, you drive by and shoot.

15:09.367 --> 15:12.412
You don't risk the time
it takes to do this.

15:12.579 --> 15:15.373
- Unless the act itself has meaning.
- <font color="#808080">CAPTAIN:</font> Come on.

15:15.749 --> 15:19.336
Somebody had a problem with the fat
boy and decided to torture him.

15:19.502 --> 15:20.503
Simple as that.

15:20.670 --> 15:22.672
In the grocery bags,
we found two receipts.

15:22.839 --> 15:25.175
That means the killer stopped
in the middle...

15:25.342 --> 15:27.469
...and made a second trip
to the supermarket.

15:27.636 --> 15:29.012
So?

15:30.096 --> 15:33.350
Hey, man, it's his thing.
I've been out in the rain all day.

15:33.516 --> 15:34.893
This is beginning.

15:35.060 --> 15:37.354
We've got one dead guy,
not three.

15:37.771 --> 15:39.564
No motive.

15:39.898 --> 15:43.526
Don't even start that big brain of
yours cooking on this, all right?

15:43.693 --> 15:46.529
Please, I'd like
to be reassigned.

15:46.696 --> 15:47.896
- <font color="#808080">MILLS:</font> What?
- <font color="#808080">CAPTAIN:</font> What?

15:47.906 --> 15:50.867
What, whoa?
What in the hell are you talking about?

15:51.326 --> 15:53.411
This can't be my last duty.

15:53.578 --> 15:55.538
It's just gonna go on
and on and on.

15:55.705 --> 15:56.748
You're retiring.

15:56.915 --> 15:59.084
Six more days
and you're all the way gone.

15:59.250 --> 16:01.461
Won't be the first time
you've left unfinished...

16:01.628 --> 16:05.173
Those other oases were taken as close
to conclusion as humanly possible.

16:05.340 --> 16:06.716
And if I may speak freely?

16:06.883 --> 16:08.218
<font color="#808080">CAPTAIN:</font>
We're all friends here.

16:08.385 --> 16:11.888
- This should not be his first assignment.
- Oh, come on, I knew it.

16:12.055 --> 16:14.182
This is not my first assignment,
you dick.

16:14.349 --> 16:15.433
It's too soon for him.

16:15.600 --> 16:18.395
Hey, man, I'm right here.
You can say that shit to my face.

16:18.561 --> 16:20.230
- Captain...
- It's too soon for you.

16:21.564 --> 16:23.733
Captain,
if we can just talk in private?

16:23.900 --> 16:25.944
This isn't working.
It's a personal thing.

16:26.111 --> 16:27.654
- Maybe...
- Just shut up, Mills.

16:27.821 --> 16:31.741
Look, I don't have anyone else
to put on this and you know it.

16:31.908 --> 16:34.703
This is Metro.
You don't just get to swap.

16:34.869 --> 16:36.496
<font color="#808080">MILLS:</font>
Give it to me.

16:36.663 --> 16:38.957
- Say what?
- Yeah, he doesn't want it, fuck him.

16:39.124 --> 16:41.251
Sorry, but see you later.
Have a nice time.

16:41.418 --> 16:44.087
- Give it to me.
- No, I'm putting you on something else.

16:46.631 --> 16:48.133
Go on, Mills.

16:48.299 --> 16:49.884
Just go on.

16:55.140 --> 16:56.850
I'm sorry, old buddy.

16:57.017 --> 17:00.520
But it looks like you're stuck
cleaning up the fat man.

17:17.454 --> 17:19.497
<font color="#808080">TALBOT:</font>
All right, here we go. Quiet down.

17:19.664 --> 17:20.707
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)</font>

17:20.874 --> 17:23.417
All right, calm down.
Calm down.

17:23.585 --> 17:25.295
Quiet down.

17:25.753 --> 17:27.839
Calm down. Quiet down.

17:28.006 --> 17:30.842
Now, here's how it's gonna work.

17:31.009 --> 17:34.929
I'll answer questions for 10 minutes
and 10 minutes only.

17:35.096 --> 17:38.433
If those questions do not come in a
calm, sane and orderly fashion...

17:38.600 --> 17:39.809
...I'm on my way out here.

17:40.018 --> 17:41.811
Detective?
Detective?

17:41.978 --> 17:44.355
- Can I have a moment of your time?
- No.

17:49.194 --> 17:52.197
I will not discuss the details
of this ongoing investigation...

17:52.363 --> 17:53.948
...so don't even bother asking.

17:56.034 --> 17:57.869
<font color="#808080">MAN 1:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(OVER RADIO)</font>
<i>I've got shopping tools...</i>

17:58.036 --> 18:00.246
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(OVER RADIO)</font>
<i>That's 25 Berlin.</i>

18:00.413 --> 18:02.332
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTERING ON RADIO)</font>

18:05.293 --> 18:07.087
<font color="#808080">MAN 2:</font>
That looks like him.

18:09.047 --> 18:11.257
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(OVER RADIO)</font>
<i>Three items for your case number.</i>

18:13.343 --> 18:16.262
- What you guys got for me?
- <font color="#808080">MAN 3:</font> Nothing yet, boss.

18:19.641 --> 18:23.394
Why don't you guys, uh,
go get a coffee, huh?

18:24.354 --> 18:26.356
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(ON TV)</font>
<i>We have this breaking story for you.</i>

18:26.523 --> 18:28.399
<i>We're going to go
live downtown...</i>

18:28.566 --> 18:31.861
<i>...where defense attorney Eli Gould
was found murdered this morning.</i>

18:32.028 --> 18:35.698
<i>District Attorney Martin Talbot
is taking questions from reporters.</i>

18:35.865 --> 18:37.367
<font color="#D900D9">(REPORTERS SHOUTING ON TV)</font>

18:37.534 --> 18:39.744
<font color="#808080">REPORTER 1:</font>
<i>There could be a conflict of interest...</i>

18:39.911 --> 18:44.040
<i>That is ridiculous to the point of being
offensive. There is no conflict whatsoever.</i>

18:44.207 --> 18:45.875
<i>And any claim that
there could be...</i>

18:46.042 --> 18:48.402
- <i>...is irresponsible.</i>
- <font color="#808080">REPORTER 2:</font> <i>Mr. Talbot, Mr. Talbot.</i>

18:48.461 --> 18:50.461
- <i>Hold on.</i>
- <font color="#808080">REPORTER 3:</font> <i>It's rumored you're far...</i>

18:50.463 --> 18:53.263
- <i>...from apprehending a suspect.</i>
- <i><font color="#808080">TALBOT:</font> I've come from a meeting...</i>

18:53.299 --> 18:55.927
<i>...of law enforcement officials
and they've assured me...</i>

18:56.886 --> 18:59.806
<i>...they have their
very best men on this.</i>

18:59.973 --> 19:05.145
<i>This will be the very definition
of swift justice.</i>

19:29.043 --> 19:30.753
<font color="#808080">CAPTAIN:</font>
Pardon me, George.

19:35.133 --> 19:37.719
- Somerset.
- Come in.

19:38.720 --> 19:41.431
- Have you heard the news?
- <font color="#808080">SOMERSET:</font> Nope, haven't heard.

19:41.598 --> 19:44.392
Eli Gould was found murdered
this morning.

19:44.559 --> 19:48.313
Someone broke into his law firm
and bled him to death.

19:48.479 --> 19:51.441
Wrote the word
"greed" on the floor.

19:56.946 --> 19:59.532
- Greed?
- <font color="#808080">CAPTAIN:</font> Yeah, in blood.

20:00.033 --> 20:02.076
Mills is heading up
the investigation.

20:02.785 --> 20:04.537
Uh, excuse me.
Excuse me?

20:05.955 --> 20:07.624
Could you not do that, please?

20:07.790 --> 20:09.167
Oh, okay.

20:10.293 --> 20:12.128
Well, good for him.

20:12.295 --> 20:15.632
What in the hell are you gonna do
with yourself out there, Somerset?

20:15.798 --> 20:17.759
Oh, I'll work,
maybe on a farm.

20:17.926 --> 20:19.135
Fix my house.

20:19.302 --> 20:20.970
Don't you feel it?

20:21.137 --> 20:23.306
Don't you feel that feeling?

20:23.473 --> 20:26.434
You're not gonna
be a cop anymore.

20:26.601 --> 20:28.645
That's the whole idea.

20:30.146 --> 20:31.940
I don't think you're leaving.

20:32.106 --> 20:34.651
Hell, you can't leave all this.

20:36.736 --> 20:38.571
Guy's out walking his dog.

20:38.738 --> 20:40.448
Gets attacked.

20:40.615 --> 20:43.326
His watch is taken,
his wallet.

20:43.493 --> 20:46.913
While he's lying there
on the sidewalk, helpless...

20:47.163 --> 20:50.375
...his attacker stabs
him in both eyes.

20:51.626 --> 20:54.295
This happened just last night
about four blocks from here.

20:55.380 --> 20:57.340
Yeah, I read about it.

20:57.507 --> 21:01.135
- I don't understand this place any longer.
- It's the way it's always been.

21:01.511 --> 21:02.512
Maybe you're right.

21:02.679 --> 21:04.013
<font color="#808080">CAPTAIN:</font>
You do this work.

21:04.180 --> 21:07.850
You were made for it and I
don't think you can deny that.

21:08.685 --> 21:10.561
Maybe I'm wrong.

21:11.396 --> 21:15.149
Oh, uh, the coroner
sent this down for you.

21:15.483 --> 21:19.362
Found them in fat boy's stomach,
mixed in with food.

21:19.529 --> 21:23.449
- Looks like plastic, little pieces of plastic.
- Set them on the desk, please.

21:27.870 --> 21:29.247
They were, uh...

21:29.414 --> 21:30.456
They were fed to him.

22:25.303 --> 22:28.097
<font color="#D900D9">(FRIDGE ENGINE RATTLING)</font>

23:10.473 --> 23:11.766
Oh, Lord.

23:19.524 --> 23:21.984
This was found on the wall
behind the refrigerator...

23:22.151 --> 23:24.320
...in the obesity murder scene.

23:25.321 --> 23:30.118
"Long is the way and hard
that out of hell leads up to light."

23:30.284 --> 23:32.120
It's from Milton.

23:32.328 --> 23:34.205
<i>Paradise Lost.</i>

23:34.497 --> 23:36.416
All right, I'm confused.

23:36.582 --> 23:39.419
It means that this is beginning.

23:40.586 --> 23:42.588
This was found
behind the same refrigerator.

23:43.089 --> 23:44.882
Written in grease.

23:45.049 --> 23:47.760
There are seven deadly sins,
captain.

23:47.927 --> 23:49.595
Gluttony.

23:51.889 --> 23:53.516
Greed.

23:55.184 --> 23:58.980
Sloth, wrath, pride, lust...

23:59.147 --> 24:00.189
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

24:00.356 --> 24:01.858
...and envy.

24:02.316 --> 24:04.235
- Seven.
- Hold on.

24:04.527 --> 24:06.612
This is not even my desk.

24:07.738 --> 24:09.782
You can expect five
more of these.

24:11.576 --> 24:12.618
Now, wait a minute.

24:14.203 --> 24:16.789
I can't get involved in this.

24:18.666 --> 24:20.084
Somerset.

24:20.251 --> 24:21.961
He wanted it.

24:23.379 --> 24:26.257
- Damn.
- I'm all over it.

24:27.425 --> 24:29.886
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font>
What's wrong with you?

24:30.052 --> 24:31.721
<font color="#D900D9">(INDISTINCT CHATTERING OUTSIDE)</font>

24:51.908 --> 24:53.242
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

25:00.082 --> 25:01.667
Where you headed?

25:04.587 --> 25:06.589
Far away from here.

25:16.015 --> 25:18.392
- <font color="#808080">SOMERSET:</font> Thanks, George.
- <font color="#808080">GEORGE:</font> How you doing?

25:18.559 --> 25:20.186
Just a few things to look up.

25:20.353 --> 25:22.271
<font color="#808080">GEORGE:</font>
Okay. Sit where you'd like.

25:22.438 --> 25:23.439
<font color="#D900D9">(MEN LAUGHING)</font>

25:23.606 --> 25:24.815
How's everybody?

25:26.067 --> 25:28.110
<font color="#808080">MAN 1:</font>
Hi, Smiley.

25:28.486 --> 25:30.780
<font color="#808080">MAN 2:</font> Come on, George,
the cards are getting cold.

25:30.947 --> 25:32.281
Duty calls.

25:32.448 --> 25:33.616
<font color="#D900D9">(SOMERSET CHUCKLES)</font>

25:48.381 --> 25:50.466
Gentlemen, gentlemen.

25:50.967 --> 25:52.009
I'll never understand.

25:53.636 --> 25:55.137
All these books...

25:55.304 --> 25:57.640
...a world of knowledge
at your fingertips.

25:57.807 --> 25:59.392
What do you do?

25:59.559 --> 26:01.310
You play poker all night.

26:01.811 --> 26:03.646
<font color="#808080">MAN 3:</font>
Hey, we got culture.

26:03.813 --> 26:05.815
Yeah, we got culture
coming out of our asses.

26:05.982 --> 26:07.108
<font color="#D900D9">(MEN LAUGH)</font>

26:08.150 --> 26:09.819
<font color="#808080">MAN 2:</font>
All right.

26:09.986 --> 26:12.029
How's this for culture?

26:12.196 --> 26:14.991
<font color="#D900D9">(BACH'S "AIR" PLAYING ON STEREO)</font>

28:04.684 --> 28:06.936
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

28:49.687 --> 28:51.480
You know, Smiley...

28:52.022 --> 28:54.150
...you're really gonna miss us.

28:55.568 --> 28:57.403
I just might.

29:40.029 --> 29:42.031
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

29:54.877 --> 29:56.879
Fucking Dante.

29:57.046 --> 30:01.425
Goddamn poetry-writing faggot
piece of shit.

30:01.592 --> 30:03.177
Fucker.

30:03.928 --> 30:05.513
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANS)</font>

30:11.060 --> 30:12.394
Yeah?

30:13.938 --> 30:15.940
Good work, officer.

30:22.738 --> 30:24.907
Thank you, Lord.

30:32.081 --> 30:34.333
Oh, I'm sorry.

30:35.376 --> 30:37.586
Be out of your way in a second.

30:49.682 --> 30:51.851
- You want your chair?
- No. You go ahead.

30:52.017 --> 30:53.435
<font color="#808080">MILLS:</font>
Yeah?

31:27.803 --> 31:29.221
<font color="#D900D9">(PHONE RINGING)</font>

31:32.016 --> 31:33.475
Phone.

31:33.976 --> 31:35.102
It's a package deal.

31:35.269 --> 31:36.312
Comes with the office.

31:41.525 --> 31:42.985
- Mills.
- <font color="#808080">TRACY:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(OVER PHONE)</font> <i>Honey.</i>

31:44.486 --> 31:46.739
- Are you okay, something wrong?
- No.

31:47.197 --> 31:51.201
You dingleberry, I, uh, told you not
to call me here when I'm working.

31:52.494 --> 31:54.163
Yeah. Why?

31:54.330 --> 31:55.915
Why?

31:56.582 --> 31:59.376
- Why?
- Come on.

32:02.755 --> 32:04.340
Okay.

32:08.010 --> 32:09.011
It's my wife.

32:09.470 --> 32:10.554
Sorry?

32:12.014 --> 32:13.474
She'd like to speak to you.

32:22.900 --> 32:25.277
Uh, this is Detective Somerset.

32:25.444 --> 32:27.363
<i>Oh, it's nice to speak with you.</i>

32:27.529 --> 32:30.199
Well, it's nice to talk to you too.

32:31.867 --> 32:34.203
I appreciate the offer, but...

32:36.914 --> 32:40.000
Well, in that case I'd be delighted.
Great.

32:40.167 --> 32:43.170
- Yes, thank you very much.
- <i>Thank you. See you later.</i>

32:43.337 --> 32:44.672
Bye.

32:47.132 --> 32:48.175
Hon, what...?

32:48.342 --> 32:49.718
<font color="#D900D9">(DIAL TONE)</font>

32:56.558 --> 32:57.851
Well?

32:58.018 --> 33:00.396
- Sorry? Oh, uh.
- What?

33:00.562 --> 33:03.107
I've been invited to a late supper
at your apartment.

33:03.273 --> 33:04.692
I accepted.

33:04.858 --> 33:07.236
At my... How's that?

33:07.403 --> 33:08.988
Tonight.

33:10.447 --> 33:12.491
<font color="#808080">WOMAN:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(OVER RADIO)</font>
<i>Twenty-one-fifty-seven.</i>

33:15.536 --> 33:17.538
Hello, men.

33:17.705 --> 33:19.873
- Hi, loser.
- Hi, idiot.

33:21.583 --> 33:22.876
This is Tracy.

33:24.003 --> 33:26.130
- Somerset.
- Hello.

33:26.296 --> 33:29.800
I'm very happy to meet you.
I've heard a lot about you.

33:29.967 --> 33:31.927
Except, of course,
your first name.

33:32.094 --> 33:33.137
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

33:33.303 --> 33:34.555
It's William.

33:35.347 --> 33:39.018
Hmm, well,
it's a good name, William.

33:39.518 --> 33:41.437
William,
I'd like you to meet David.

33:41.603 --> 33:44.148
- David, this is William.
- Okay, all right, I'm gonna...

33:44.314 --> 33:45.441
I'll be right back.

33:45.607 --> 33:47.735
How are the kids?
Good, they're in the room.

33:47.901 --> 33:49.361
Come on in.

33:50.654 --> 33:52.322
Oh, good dogs.

33:52.489 --> 33:55.367
How are you, good dogs?
How are you, pretty?

33:55.534 --> 33:57.202
<font color="#D900D9">(DOGS BARKING)</font>

33:57.369 --> 33:59.121
How are you?

34:00.914 --> 34:02.458
How are you?

34:03.292 --> 34:04.710
You are?

34:06.336 --> 34:08.297
<font color="#808080">SOMERSET:</font> Smells good.
What?

34:08.464 --> 34:09.882
Uh.
Oh.

34:10.049 --> 34:11.675
Yeah.
I mean, thank you.

34:11.842 --> 34:13.010
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH CHUCKLE)</font>

34:13.177 --> 34:16.722
Um, please have a seat, if you like.
Would you like something to drink?

34:16.889 --> 34:18.348
Uh, no. No, thanks.

34:18.514 --> 34:21.018
- I'll wait.
- Okay, you can just throw that anywhere.

34:21.185 --> 34:25.522
You'll have to excuse all this mess.
You know, we're still unpacking.

34:27.733 --> 34:29.985
I understand you two
were high school sweethearts.

34:30.152 --> 34:31.320
<font color="#808080">TRACY:</font>
Mm-hm.

34:32.780 --> 34:34.739
Pretty hokey, huh?

34:35.532 --> 34:37.326
You know something?

34:37.534 --> 34:40.704
I knew on our first date that this
was the guy I was gonna marry.

34:40.871 --> 34:42.414
- Really?
- Mm-hm.

34:43.165 --> 34:45.918
He was the funniest
guy I'd ever met.

34:50.255 --> 34:51.297
Really?

34:54.592 --> 34:56.929
Well, it's kind of rare
nowadays, you know.

34:57.096 --> 35:00.849
I mean, that level
of commitment.

35:05.312 --> 35:07.147
Oh, don't worry.

35:07.314 --> 35:10.192
I won't wear it to the dinner table.
No, ha, ha.

35:10.359 --> 35:13.862
I, uh... You know, no matter
how often I see guns, I just...

35:14.029 --> 35:16.990
I can't get used to them.

35:17.825 --> 35:18.909
Same here.

35:21.870 --> 35:24.373
<font color="#D900D9">(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

35:29.253 --> 35:30.879
Why aren't you married, William?

35:31.046 --> 35:33.215
Oh, Trace,
what the hell?

35:33.382 --> 35:35.509
I was close once.

35:36.176 --> 35:37.302
It just didn't happen.

35:37.719 --> 35:39.763
It surprises me.

35:39.930 --> 35:41.932
It really does.

35:42.933 --> 35:44.393
Well...

35:45.227 --> 35:49.857
Anyone who spends a significant amount
of time with me finds me disagreeable.

35:50.440 --> 35:51.817
Just ask your husband.

35:51.984 --> 35:53.318
Very true.

35:53.485 --> 35:55.737
Very, very true.

35:56.071 --> 35:58.532
So how long have you lived here?

35:58.949 --> 35:59.992
Too long.

36:04.204 --> 36:05.289
How are you liking it?

36:07.166 --> 36:11.587
You know, takes time,
settle in.

36:12.546 --> 36:13.964
It'll be good.

36:14.131 --> 36:16.258
Well, you get numb after awhile.

36:16.425 --> 36:17.426
<font color="#D900D9">(DOGS BARKING)</font>

36:17.593 --> 36:19.094
There are things to any city.

36:19.261 --> 36:21.555
<font color="#D900D9">(TRAIN APPROACHING)</font>

36:21.722 --> 36:23.140
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING)</font>

36:25.559 --> 36:26.935
Subway.

36:27.102 --> 36:30.063
- It will go away in a minute.
- It's nothing.

36:32.941 --> 36:34.902
Real estate guy.

36:35.068 --> 36:36.403
Fucking piece of...

36:36.570 --> 36:38.363
Sorry, honey.
He's...

36:38.530 --> 36:40.866
He shows us the place
a few times.

36:41.033 --> 36:42.910
I think he's good.
He's efficient.

36:43.076 --> 36:44.953
Tracy really likes him.

36:45.120 --> 36:49.458
Then I start wondering why will he only
bring us here five minutes at a time, yeah?

36:49.625 --> 36:51.335
We found out the first night.

36:51.752 --> 36:56.757
The soothing, relaxing,
vibrating home, huh?

36:57.424 --> 36:59.134
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

37:01.053 --> 37:02.846
<font color="#D900D9">(SNICKERS)</font>

37:03.013 --> 37:04.848
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH CHUCKLE)</font>

37:05.015 --> 37:06.808
I'm sorry.

37:07.726 --> 37:10.687
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH LAUGH)</font>

37:11.939 --> 37:13.357
<font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

37:13.523 --> 37:15.442
Yeah, all right, laugh it up.

37:18.862 --> 37:20.530
I don't know why
you're laughing.

37:24.451 --> 37:26.536
All right, already.

37:30.207 --> 37:31.792
The guy would've
had to get in...

37:31.959 --> 37:34.503
...before the office was closed
and security tightened.

37:34.670 --> 37:36.505
Now, Gould would've
been working late.

37:36.672 --> 37:39.716
I'm certain. He was the biggest
defense lawyer in town.

37:39.883 --> 37:40.926
Infamous, really.

37:41.093 --> 37:43.303
Now listen, body was found
on Tuesday morning.

37:43.470 --> 37:47.641
The office was closed on Monday, which
means the guy could've gotten in Friday...

37:47.808 --> 37:52.062
...laid low till the cleaning crew left then
had his way with Gould all day Saturday...

37:52.229 --> 37:54.773
...Sunday, maybe even Monday.

37:55.148 --> 37:56.692
Hey, look at this.

37:56.858 --> 37:59.111
Gould was bound,
right arm almost free.

37:59.278 --> 38:00.779
He was handed a
butcher's knife.

38:02.864 --> 38:04.574
Check out the scale.

38:04.741 --> 38:05.993
<font color="#808080">SOMERSET:</font>
A pound of flesh?

38:06.368 --> 38:08.120
Yeah.

38:13.048 --> 38:15.922
"One pound of flesh,
no more, no less."

38:16.047 --> 38:19.648
"No cartilage, no bone,
but only flesh."

38:19.673 --> 38:21.717
- <i>Merchant of Venice.</i>
- Didn't see it.

38:21.883 --> 38:25.053
"This task done and
he would go free."

38:25.220 --> 38:28.390
I'm telling you that chair
was soaked through with sweat.

38:28.557 --> 38:30.309
Of course.

38:30.726 --> 38:33.770
The killer would've wanted Gould
to take his time...

38:33.937 --> 38:37.441
...to sit and decide
which out to make first.

38:37.607 --> 38:39.109
Imagine it.

38:39.276 --> 38:41.570
There's a gun in your face.

38:41.820 --> 38:44.656
Which part of your body
is expendable?

38:44.823 --> 38:46.658
What about the love handle?

38:46.825 --> 38:49.578
Cut along the side of
his own stomach.

38:50.245 --> 38:52.748
All right, let's take a
fresh look at these.

38:52.914 --> 38:55.208
Even though the corpse is there,
look through it.

38:55.375 --> 38:57.085
Edit out the initial shock.

38:57.252 --> 39:02.674
Trick is to find one item,
one detail and focus on it...

39:02.841 --> 39:05.385
...until it's an
exhausted possibility.

39:05.552 --> 39:07.346
- Just gonna get another beer.
- Beer?

39:07.512 --> 39:09.723
Uh, wine, please.

39:16.688 --> 39:18.106
<font color="#D900D9">(FRIDGE OPENS)</font>

39:18.273 --> 39:19.775
He's preaching.

39:20.150 --> 39:21.735
He's punishing.

39:23.528 --> 39:26.865
The sins were used
in medieval sermons.

39:27.282 --> 39:29.993
There were seven cardinal virtues
and seven deadly sins...

39:30.160 --> 39:31.453
...used as teaching tools.

39:31.620 --> 39:34.122
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
like in, uh, The Parson's Tale and...

39:34.289 --> 39:35.791
What's this? Uh, Dante.

39:35.957 --> 39:38.168
- You read them?
- Yeah.

39:38.335 --> 39:41.421
Well, parts.
Hey, remember in, uh, Purgatory?

39:41.588 --> 39:43.965
Dante and his buddy,
they're climbing up the hill...

39:44.132 --> 39:46.301
...they're checking out
all the sinners, yeah?

39:46.468 --> 39:49.763
- Yeah, the seven terraces of purgation.
- Yeah, yeah, right.

39:49.930 --> 39:53.183
But there, pride comes first,
not gluttony.

39:53.350 --> 39:57.354
Yeah, well, for now, let's just consider that
the books were the killer's inspiration.

39:57.521 --> 40:00.982
The sermons
were about atonement for sin.

40:01.233 --> 40:03.276
These murders are
like forced attrition.

40:03.985 --> 40:06.029
- Forced what?
- Attrition.

40:06.196 --> 40:08.990
It's when you regret your sins,
but not because you love God.

40:09.157 --> 40:12.202
Oh, like because someone's sticking
a fucking gun in your face.

40:12.369 --> 40:13.829
Mm-hm.

40:16.206 --> 40:18.583
- No fingerprints.
- Nope.

40:18.750 --> 40:22.003
- Totally unrelated victims.
- Yup.

40:22.170 --> 40:24.631
And no witnesses of any kind.

40:24.798 --> 40:26.466
Which I don't get.

40:26.633 --> 40:29.886
Because the fucker
had to get back out.

40:30.387 --> 40:34.975
Well, in any major city, minding
your own business is a science.

40:35.392 --> 40:39.020
The first thing they teach women in
rape prevention is never cry for help.

40:39.855 --> 40:41.356
Always yell "Fire."

40:41.523 --> 40:42.816
Nobody answers to "Help."

40:42.983 --> 40:44.901
You holler "fire,"
they come running.

40:45.318 --> 40:46.736
That's fucked up.

40:46.903 --> 40:50.198
He must've left another
puzzle piece.

40:51.867 --> 40:52.909
You know what?

40:53.076 --> 40:56.371
Thank you for talking this
out, but I gotta sleep.

40:56.746 --> 41:00.167
- Walk the dogs.
- This is just strictly to satisfy my curiosity.

41:00.333 --> 41:03.044
- I'm still leaving at the end of the week.
- Oh, shit.

41:03.211 --> 41:04.838
No, wait, wait.

41:06.089 --> 41:08.842
Gould's wife. She was
out of town at the time.

41:09.009 --> 41:12.220
- So this means she saw something.
- What if it's a threat?

41:12.387 --> 41:15.056
Well, I put her in a safe house.
She wasn't too happy about it.

41:15.223 --> 41:17.017
<font color="#D900D9">(RUMBLING)</font>

41:17.184 --> 41:19.227
<font color="#D900D9">(DOGS BARKING)</font>

41:24.399 --> 41:26.860
<font color="#808080">SOMERSET:</font> What if it isn't
something she has seen?

41:27.027 --> 41:31.114
But something she's supposed to see,
but hasn't been given a chance?

41:31.615 --> 41:32.991
Yeah, okay. What?

41:33.450 --> 41:35.118
I don't know.

41:36.703 --> 41:38.997
But that's the one thing.

42:24.042 --> 42:25.669
<font color="#808080">MILLS:</font>
Sign us in.

42:25.835 --> 42:27.921
Gotta see Mrs. Gould.

42:28.421 --> 42:30.423
<font color="#808080">GOULD:</font>
treat me like a prisoner.

42:30.590 --> 42:33.760
Why do you have a phone if I can't
make long distance phone calls?

42:33.927 --> 42:35.011
Mrs. Gould?

42:35.178 --> 42:36.596
<font color="#808080">GOULD:</font>
Don't treat people like this.

42:37.305 --> 42:39.641
<font color="#D900D9">(GOULD CRYING)</font>

42:41.643 --> 42:44.104
Mrs. Gould, I am sorry.
I truly am.

42:44.896 --> 42:46.606
I don't understand.

42:47.315 --> 42:51.861
Okay, I need you to look at
each photo very carefully.

42:52.028 --> 42:56.992
Look and see if there's anything
strange or out of place.

42:57.158 --> 42:58.159
Um, anything at all.

42:59.202 --> 43:01.246
I don't see anything.
You're sure?

43:01.413 --> 43:03.915
Please, I just...
I can't do this right now.

43:04.082 --> 43:05.709
Okay.

43:06.167 --> 43:07.752
<font color="#808080">SOMERSET:</font> <font color="#D900D9">(WHISPERS)</font>
It's got to be now.

43:07.919 --> 43:10.213
There may be something
we haven't seen.

43:19.055 --> 43:20.473
<font color="#808080">GOULD:</font>
Wait.

43:20.640 --> 43:22.892
- What?
- Here.

43:26.271 --> 43:29.858
This painting, it's upside down.

43:37.198 --> 43:39.242
- You sure your men didn't move this?
- No, no.

43:39.409 --> 43:42.120
Those shots were taken
before forensics.

43:45.206 --> 43:46.666
Nothing.

43:47.584 --> 43:50.211
There's gotta be something.

44:00.555 --> 44:03.391
- Moved the screws to rehang it.
- Yep.

44:07.562 --> 44:09.439
What the fuck is that?

44:10.523 --> 44:12.275
Switchblade.

44:20.200 --> 44:22.118
Goddamn it.

44:25.205 --> 44:28.083
There must be something.

44:32.879 --> 44:35.382
He didn't paint the
fucking thing.

44:43.014 --> 44:46.059
No, he's fucking with us,
that's what he's doing.

44:47.102 --> 44:49.145
See this? This is us.

44:49.771 --> 44:50.814
Yeah.

44:50.980 --> 44:52.607
Just wait a minute.

44:55.026 --> 44:57.153
Now Somerset's climbing
on the furniture.

